     Pets do not eat harm touch anymore, this was patched absolutely ages ago, this patch was in before FV was live.<br>
<br>
*spell rank#9<br>
     This pet is excelent, it's around lv4 and you can give it mage summoned 'magic' wepons so can kill wisps a lot easyer than other classes.<br>
<br>
*spell rank#15<br>
     This pet is another good one, half your lv it seems able to hit mobs to give a good DPS increase.<br>
<br>
*spell rank#22<br>
     This pet is not that good, it's half your lv and has problems hitting mobs, it is a good inrease in DPS your lv but not neer to how good the previouse two were.<br>
<br>
*spell rank#30<br>
     This pet is ok, around lv15, like previouse one it has problems hitting mobs, STR buff and minor dex buff helps it a lot, use your pet buff to make the most out of it, the pet buff 'really' helps this pet when you get it.<br>
<br>
*spell rank#39<br>
     This is out most useless pet, its obsolete at the lv you get it, and your next upgrade is at lv49, so you have to use a pet for 10 lvs when it is useless at the lv you get it!!<br>
<br>
*spell rank#49<br>
     This is a good pet, does not always dual wield, have to give it wepons to dual it wont do it with fist, with wepons it can knock up some good damage.. i find the best for this pet is veliouse wepons from tower of shadow..the ones with +str or +dex..they can bump the pets damage up significantly, the pet buff REALLY helps this pet. Very good spell.<br>
<br>
*spell rank#52<br>
     This pet is REALLY good, your first really really usefull pet, use it in groups, use it when you can, it's DPS is really worth the mana and time to cast it. Solo it is the difference between life and death.<br>
<br>
*spell rank#58<br>
     This pet is amazing, it lifetaps so can heal it'self so lasts longer than the other pets due to healing through reposts, it also has lovely DPS and when buffed is rather good.<br>
      For a test, somone said i could not kill Bulthars because they had massive hit points, i was killing them ages ago without a problem so i thought i would rip through them fast - the 58 pet rips through them like a gnome on a snow bunny in hunting season.<br>
      This is the first pet that will do scary DPS compared to shadowknight wepons on FV.. as when you are a shadowknight you end up either agro kiting and fear kiting in places, this pet is just scary when it has the time to attack the mob with it's buff... and the mob does not kill it, really really worth getting to 58 just for this pet alone.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I have seen my 52 pet out damage warriors in my group, this pet can do some nice damage in some situations.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
As for other functions of a pet, you can use a pet for FD splitting in variouse ways.<br>
<br>
You can use a pet for pulling through areas that you cannot get a spell into or a line of site.<br>
<br>
You can use pets for mob tracking, aka tracking spawn points of mobs in Eastern wastes that pop the dwarf (the spawn point counts as a mob, because it is an ingame trigger, same should work for things like construct traps in DN)<br>
<br>
Can even use your pet as a sacrifice to give you some distance on a pull or even to escape from a mob.<br>
<br>
Interupting in duals is rather good also on a PVP aspect.<br>
<br>
You can even equip some wepons on your pet at higher lvs to get certain procs to aid you, gnoll whips will be resisted..but in theory they are nice... there are some pretty cheep proc wepons you can get that will help your pet though.<br>
<br>
